description: The Jersey Shore of super villains crashes Seattle to stream Green Arrow's death over the Internet! It's the final fight between Green Arrow and Rush: media maven vs. media star! The whole world's watching on their QPhones and QPads. Why aren't you? Plus: Queen Industries launches their new initiative – and issues a challenge to the world!
name: Green Arrow's Last Stand

description:
Read the finale of our coolest comic strip yet in the latest issue of Batman: The Brave and the Bold! Will Batman and Green Lantern be able to defeat the monstrous meteoroid before he reshapes planet Earth in 'The Menace Called Robert'.

Also inside this issue:

  • 'Batman's Ultimate Team Ups' feature
  • Batman's Secret Files: Captain Marvel
  • Pull-out poster
  • Episode Guide: 'Trials of the Demon!'
  • Brain-bending puzzles and activities
  • Win Harry Potter LEGO bundles!
  • Bat Signals: Your letters and artwork
name: 'The Menace Called Robert' comic strip - Part Two!

volume.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
A brand new comic strip kicks off in the latest issue of Batman: The Brave and the Bold! Batman teams up with the new Green Lantern on the block, Guy Gardner! Can they work together to defeat the monstrous Manhunters?

Also inside this issue:

  • Meet the Manhunters, the universe's first intergalactic police force!
  • Batman's Secret Files: Guy Gardner
  • Pull-out poster
  • Learn to draw Blue Beetle
  • Brain-bending puzzles and activities
  • Win LEGO Alien Conquest prizes!
  • Bat Signals: Your letters and artwork
name: 'Man-Hunted' comic strip - Part One!

volume.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
This new comic strip reached its thrilling conclusion in the latest issue of Batman: The Brave and the Bold! While Guy Gardner's taking in the manhunters single-handedly, Batman is left to confront the evil alien, Lobo! It looks as if the duo is outnumbered - what next for Batman and Guy?!

Also inside this issue:

  • Spacewarp! Play our awesome game for two or more players - can you help Batman and Guy Gardner outsmart and outrun the menacing Manhunters?
  • When Aliens Attack! We look at some of the aliens we love to hate!
  • Batman's Secret Files: Lobo
  • Pull-out poster
  • Brain-bending puzzles and activities
  • Win Green Lantern DVDs and LEGO Hero Factory prizes!
  • Bat Signals: Your letters and artwork
name: 'Man-Hunted' comic strip - Part Two!

volume.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
Batman and Robin #15: Batman and Robin Must Die - Part Three: The Knight, Death and the Devil

Commissioner Gordon is strung out on Pyg's addiction disease, Dick Grayson has been kidnapped by Doctor Hurt and Damian Wayne is about to be let loose like a rabid dog on the whole group!

Batman: The Return of Bruce Wayne - Part Five: Masquerade

Fighting his way back to the present Bruce Wayne is fast becoming Darkseid's favourite weapon of mass destruction. He lands in '30s Gotham with a sharp suit, a femme fatale and a case to solve.

Batman 700: Time and the Batman - Tomorrow

It's New Year. Gotham City is being held to ransom by a madman called January. Will Damian Wayne's Batman survive the threat of marauding zombie jokers and neurotoxic laughing death rain?
name: Batman and Robin #15; Batman: The Return of Bruce Wayne #5; Batman #700

description:
Son of Superman: Parts 3 and 4 of 4

It's the thrilling conclusion to Jon Kent's first adventure! After discovering that his father is alive, Jon is faced with his toughest battle yet! Lex Luthor's nefarious scheme comes to fruition as a betrayal from within the Justice League ignites a super heroic smackdown!

Green Lantern: Branded

It's the ultimate Super Hero team-up as Green Lantern and Batman join forces to take down the villainous Tattooed Man!

Plus:

  • Green Lantern Batman Poster by acclaimed artist Ethan Van Sciver!
  • Win the Green Lantern movie on Blu-ray™ and DVD!
The Tick finds himself in Washington DC and becomes the target of the politics of personal destruction. A fictional story if ever I heard one.
name: Mr. Tick Goes To Washington
The Tick's Life In A Day

description:
Season 4 preview!

You won't believe the cool stuff coming up this year in Star Wars: The Clone Wars. In this issue of the show's official comic, feast your eyes on a gallery of teasers from the first six episodes of the season! Plus, check out our awesome guide to Episode 4.01, 'Water War'!

Brand new comic strip: 'The Only Good Clanker'

Below the illuminated skies of Bogoa, a company from the 212th Attack Battalion, led by Obi-Wan Kenobi and Commander Cody, has finally broken the droid stranglehold. But despite helping to defeat the invading force, one clone is about to discover that a trooper's work is never done...!

Underwater Action!

The Jedi and the clone troopers they lead have a hard enough time fighting on land and in space - but imagine what it's like waging war underwater! Find out all about what it takes in this issue's cool feature!

Also in this issue:

Captain Ackbar: The lowdown on Prince Lee-Char's right-hand man!

Competition: Win Star Wars: The Clone Wars action figures from Hasbro!

Lots of fun games and cool puzzles

Clone Zone: Your letters, pictures, and photos

The Wizard of Oz is back and the Mangaboos have him! These deadly vegetable people also have Dorothy, her cousin Zeb, their horse Jim and kitten Eureka. To save their lives, the humbug Wizard must win a contest of magic against a real Sorcerer—using only his wits and nine tiny piglets. The beloved Oz adaptation continues with the critically acclaimed and Eisner Award winning team-up of Eric Shanower and Skottie Young.

What is to become of the mutants who side with Cyclops after the big split? And what does it have to do with the resurrected Mister Sinister?

The new Extinction team
name: Everything is Sinister

description: THE SILVER AGE TEEN TITANS ARCHIVES VOL. 1 reprints the earliest adventures of the world's greatest team of teenaged super-hero sidekicks from the 1960s. Presenting the first meeting of Robin, Kid Flash, Wonder Girl and Aqualad, this beautiful hardcover edition chronicles the formation of the Teen Titans and their original uncanny exploits. Featuring appearances by Speedy and Beast Boy, this wonderful book also includes classic battles against Mister Twister and the Ant, as well as the creation of the first Titans Lair.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: The Silver Age Teen Titans Archives

description: Massacre's crusade of blood continues, and the only one standing in his way is Batwing, who finds himself fighting alongside a legendary hero of Africa: the mighty Thunder Fall! As more heroes are targeted by this madman, the mystery of why begins to unfold, as does the story of Batwing's dark past.
name: We Have Blood on Our Hands

description: Maxine and Buddy swim to the heart of the Life Web and come face to face with the Totems...caretakers of the Red. But before they can get answers, the Hunters Three attack. Meanwhile, Ellen and Cliff fight for their lives back home. The Hunt heats up!
name: The Hunt, Part Three: Totems

description: The moon has declared war on Earth, and now its emissaries have landed. All over the world these lunar antibodies have absorbed our buildings, our pets and our neighbors, crafting monstrous bodies to tear our world apart. Fighting on the front lines: new recruits Apollo and Midnighter. Plus, Harry Tanner – the Eminence of Blades – makes a play for power that threatens to cut Stormwatch in two!
name: The Dark Side, Part Three

description: Hawk and Dove are in for the fight of their lives when the deadly villain Condor makes his move! But what secrets does he know about the avatars that power Hawk and Dove, and will one of our heroes be willing to kill to get it? More important, will Hawk be able to protect the President of the United States from Condor and his mysterious partner?
name: When a White House Runs Red…

description: 20Sometimes even the best intel isn't good enough. Rock and his men find themselves surrounded by dozens of guerrilla fighters when their last clip runs out – but bullets might not be their only weapon. Also: Ice and Tracker come face-to-face with a family of human shields. Can they clear the area in time for an incoming evac without harming innocents?
name: Last Clip; Navy Seals: Human Shields, Part 3

description: The Cobra Civil War races toward its climax! Trapped in Springfield seconds away from extermination by a rogue B.A.T., Team Alpha, lead by Flint, resorts to desperate measures that may not see them out of Springfield alive! Meanwhile, Mainframe scrambles to save the Tuna, a captured submarine now manned by a Joe crew, as Cobra's cyber attack sinks it to the bottom of the sea !
name: Cobra Civil War Part 19

description: Introducing the world's worst super hero! When a low-level S.H.I.E.L.D. agent gets a hold of Hank Pym's new Ant-Man suit, you know the Marvel Universe is in trouble. He's not concerned with saving the world or helping others - he's concerned with getting through the day and getting a leg up on life. He's not going to use his powers responsibly, he's going to use them for the betterment of himself. He's Ant-Man, a new "hero" for the modern world. If you thought Robert Kirkman pushed the boundaries fo what could be in a Marvel Comic with Marvel Zombies, just wait until you see what he does in here! Collects The Irredeemable Ant-Man #1-12 and material from Civil War: Choosing Sides.
name: The World's Most Unlikeable Super Hero

description: Zombie gangs, killer robots, beasts beyond reckoning, and stuck in the middle is Goon! But can the titular powerhouse resist the wicked allure of femme fatale guest star Roxi Dlite--the 2010 Queen of Burlesque? Will Franky be able to pick his tongue off of the ground before issue's end?! Find out the stunning and sultry answers in a new madcap issue of The Goon!

The fight for Catwoman's treasures is ON! She's been double-crossed by Two-Face, and has to go deep into enemy territory to regain her property...right into the heart of Hugo Strange's Arkham City! Strange wants nothing more than to capture her, Two-Face and even Batman. Will the pull of priceless treasures prove to be a trap for all three?
name: Inside Job (Part 3)

description: America's longest-running magazine of classic comics Now has twice as many pages of strips as the earlier version, on better paper, and includes 8 pages of full-color comic strips. See The Phantom in "Return of the Sky Band," Flash Gordon in "Journey Across Mongo," Mandrake the Magician in "The World of Z," and Tarzan in "Tarzan and the Roman Legion." Plus, other favorites like Little Orphan Steve Canyon, Modesty Blaise, and more.
name: Modesty Blaise

description:
ENEMY ACE ARCHIVES VOL. 1 collects the earliest tales of Hans von Hammer, the greatest fighter pilot of World War I. Utilizing superb characterization, these elegantly crafted stories offer an intriguing and rare look at war by presenting it through the eyes of "the enemy." Although a German soldier, Enemy Ace must still struggle with the agony of survival and the senseless deaths of young men. This book shows that war is not simply good guys versus bad guys but instead human versus human.

Forward by Joe Kubert.

Collects Our Army at War #151, 153 & 155, Showcase #57-58 and Star Spangled War Stories #138-142.

Story Titles

  • Our Army At War No. 151 - Enemy Ace - February 1965
  • Out Army At War No. 153 - Flaming Bait! - April 1965
  • Our Army At War No. 155 - Fokker Fury! - June 1965
  • Showcase No. 57 - Killer Of The Skies! - July-August 1965
  • Showcase No. 58 - The Hunters -- And The Hunted! - September-October 1965
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 138 - The Slayers And The Slain! - April-May 1968
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 139 - Death Whispers -- Death Screams! - June-July 1968
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 140 - The Face Of The Hangman - August-September 1968
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 141 - The Bull - October-November 1968
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 142 - Vengeance Is A Harpy! - December-January 1968-1969
name: Volume 1

description:
Death stalks the skies above Europe once more in this second volume of THE ENEMY ACE ARCHIVES, reprinting the classic adventures of World War I German fighter ace Hans von Hammer from the pages of STAR SPANGLED WAR STORIES from 1969 through 1976!

Foreword by Robert Klein and Michael Usland.

Collects Star Spangled War Stories #143-150, 152, 158, 181-183 & 200.

Story Titles

  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 143 - The Devil's General: Air War Of World War 1 - February-March 1969
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 144 - Death Takes No Holiday! - April-May 1969
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 145 - Return Of The Hangman - June-July 1969
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 146 - Enemy Ace - August-September 1969
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 147 - A Grave In The Sky! - October-November 1969
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 148 - Luck Is A Puppy Named Schatzi! - December 1969-January 1970
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 149 - Reach For The Heavens - February-March 1970
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 150 - 3 Graves To Home! - April-May 1970
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 152 - Rain Above... Mud Below! - August-September 1970
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 158 - Special Pin-Up: Enemy Ace -- The Hammer Of Hell - August-September 1971
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 181 - Hell's Angels! Part One: The Hammer Of Hell! - June-July 1974
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 182 - Hell's Angels! Part Two: The Maverick Ace! - September-October 1974
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 183 - Hell's Angels! Part Three: To End In Flames! - November-December 1974
  • Star Spangled War Stories No. 200 - Shooting Star - June-July 1976
name: Volume 2

description: After a lengthy transient existence of life on the run, Jack Lynch decides that his Gen protégés deserve to experience some luxury and pampering. Relocating in New York City, Fairchild, Grunge, Rainmaker, Burnout, and Freefall get setup in a posh high-rise hotel and see how the other half live. But as they proceed to enjoy the high-life a little too much, the suddenly high profile Gen-Actives gain the unwanted attention of a new set of villains. Suddenly the young heroes downtime is interrupted by a femme fatale who turns Grunge into a Gorilla and a mad psychopath who plans on taking over the world with mind-controlling lingerie.
name: TPB

description: The heroes of Gen13 attempt to rebuild their shattered world in this new collection featuring issues #21-26. After jumping through an I.O. teleportation device at the close of their last adventure, the GEN13 kids find themselves in a radically changed world they never expected.
name: TPB

description: A new trade paperback collecting the beautifully illustrated 6-issue miniseries! Join Fletcher Arrowsmith as he embarks on a voyage of self-discovery in an alternate universe in which magic plays a part in World War I! Arrowsmith needs to choose sides in the struggle, but soon realizes that if the so-called good guys win, the world will be forever changed. But will it be for better or worse? Will he be able to find his place — and himself — in this world? Plus, this collection includes the 8-page preview story that introduced Fletcher Arrowsmith!
name: So Smart In Their Fine Uniforms

volume.name: Arrowsmith: So Smart in Their Fine Uniforms

description: THE END!
name: Out Of Step, Part 5

description:
"THE LAZARUS TREE," Part Two

Tensions in Kyauktada are reaching a boiling point. Moriarty discovers bizarre facts behind a recent spate of killings, a drug-trafficking ring that is linked to his missing friend, and a mass-murder in the jungle that threatens to expose his endgame.
name: The Lazarus Tree, Part Two

description:
"THE GATHERING STORM," Part One

Since his awakening in the pages of SPAWN #185, Jim Downing has been at constant odds with his new life as a Hellspawn. Now, following his confrontation with Clown, Jim is ready to step from the shadows and claim his place as a new messiah for the Digital Age.

The future starts NOW!!!
name: The Gathering Storm, Part 1 (of 6)

description:
The magic has returned! But, this time…the light has grown dark.

The journey back through the ages continues, shedding light on the fates of the bearers of the light, the Samsuras that came before Malikai. As he discovers more about the unbridled magic surging within him, as well as the inherent dangers that can accompany such power, the present day will finally take center stage in the timeline of the Soulfire universe! Yet, all bearers are not effortlessly pure of heart, and those of the past have often found solace in the dark pleasures of others’ suffering—even those who may possess the wondrous ability of flight.

New adversaries, exotic locations, and a fresh cast of exciting characters, including some from the Soulfire Universe’s long forgotten past, reign supreme in this epic third SOULFIRE volume!
name: The Other Side

description: Sequel to Days of Future Past. Reprints Fantastic Four Annual 23, New Mutants Annual 6, X-Factor Annual 5 & X-Men Annual 14.
name: TPB

description: The empire strikes back! A flaw emerges in Sonja's plan, her ruse has pulled the emperor's forces south and exposed the capital - but that means his army is at Sogoria's doorstep. Her allies desperately try to hold the fort, while Sonja storms the imperial capital.

Redhand, the villainous master of disguise and martial arts from Kato's past, has defeated not one, not two, but all three of Century City's heroes. Green Hornet fell, then the new Kato, and finally the elder Kato. Redhand is poised to end what two generations of heroes have fought to attain. Now, in the finale of this four-issue arc, help arrives from the least likely source of all. Will it be enough, or will Century City have to accept a new villain, a REAL villain, in Green Hornet's place?
name: The Devil You Know, Part Four

description: As Earth remains in the grip of terror, and society’s heroes desperately try to defend its people, the Plutonian’s rage has been driven to heights by revelations about his past. After sacrifice, hope, and death, is it truly too late to stop the Plutonian? This arc-ending issue will leave IRREDEEMABLE fans reeling! Find out what everyone is talking about in the latest installment of Mark Waid’s multiple Eisner and Harvey Award-nominated superhero series!

Roger Langridge — the Harvey Award winner behind THE MUPPET SHOW and THOR: THE MIGHTY AVENGER — continues his all new side-splitting adventure that can only be explained as…SNARKED! Journey with Langridge as he pulls the carpet out from under such Lewis Carroll classics as The Walrus and The Carpenter, Through the Looking Glass, and The Hunting of the Snark, creating an all new world of humorous grandeur. Join Princess Scarlett as she, her baby brother Rusty, and the Walrus and the Carpenter outwit the villainous royal advisors to save the Kingdom and set sail in search of the missing Red King. It’s a rip-roaring issue that you won’t want to miss!
name: Fit the Second: Enter the Gryphon

description:
"Spider-Island, Epilogue: The Naked City"

*It's the morning after for New York City. See how everything has changed for Peter Parker and the spider-crew now that he's once again the world's only Spider-Man...or is he?
name: Spider-Island, Epilogue: The Naked City

description:
Sixth and final Dan Dare Annual - a 64 page hardcover UK annual from 1990 - spin-off from the Eagle.

There are no writer or artist credits.

  • Cover: David Pugh (Dan Dare and Digby)
  • Dan Dare - untitled 'The Water Beasts' (art: Keith Watson?)
  • Hall of fame - a look at Dan's friends and enemies
  • Keith Watson interview
  • Digby (art: Keith Page)
  • Dan Dare - Funfair of Death (reprint from the Eagle Annual 1971) (art: Eric Eden)
  • Dan Dare - untitled 'Mine Disaster' (art: Vanyo)
name: Dan Dare Annual 1991

description: Following the deaths of Batman and Martian Manhunter – both charter members of the Justice League of America – a new team of heroes arises, determined to stop evil from ever striking. But when the JLA's foe Prometheus plans his revenge on the heroes, will this new team be ready to pay the cost for the justice they seek? Collected from the 7-issue miniseries!
name: HC/TPB

description: The hit cartoon show gets the "JPA" treatment, as the episodes "Initiation" and "For the Man Who Has Everything" are adapted! These stories feature high-quality screen-captures and dialogue straight from the show's scripts!
name: TBA

volume.name: Justice League Unlimited: Jam Packed Action

description: Now kids can read their favorite episodes of KIDS' WB! shows! The first volume in a new line of books featuring Mucha Lucha, Xiaolin Showdown, Teen Titans Go! and Scooby Doo! Each installment will feature favorite episodes from each series, adapted into comic-book form utilizing high-quality art reproductions from the actual show! This volume will feature four stories, and they're a guaranteed hit with any fan of the shows!
name: TPB

description: An amazing new volume collecting NEW TEEN TITANS #28-34 and NEW TEEN TITANS ANNUAL #2! Tara Markov is rescued from kidnappers by Changeling. Thus begins her quest to use her powers over earth and gravity for good, and join the team as Terra. Does this obnoxious young powerhouse have what it takes to be a team player?
name: TPB

volume.name: The New Teen Titans: Terra Incognito

description: One of the most popular Titans members ever is the focus of this all-new collection featuring THE NEW TEEN TITANS #38, TALES OF THE NEW TEEN TITANS #50, THE NEW TITANS #50-55, TITANS/OUTSIDERS SECRET FILES 2003 and much more!
name: TPB

volume.name: The New Teen Titans: Who Is Donna Troy?

description:
52 page spin-off Holiday Special from Eagle starring Dan Dare - with original comic strips, features and puzzle pages.

There are no creator credits listed in the special.

Cover: Keith Watson (Dan Dare)

  • Dan Dare - untitled 'Galactic Collector' (art: John Ridgway)
  • Dan Dare - untitled 'Volcano' (art: Ian Kennedy)
  • Digby - The Guinea Pig (text story) (reprint from Dan Dare Space Book 1953)
  • The Mekon - untitled 'Black Heart'

Articles:

  • Meet Dan Dare (character bio)
  • The Mekon of Mekonta (character bio)
  • Real Heroes (a look at Willie, Flamer and Stripey)
  • Interview with David Pugh
  • Dan in Disguise
  • The Fantastic Cities, Bases and Landscapes of Dan Dare (Cryptos - Mekonta - Saturnia - Phantos - McHoo's Base - Terra Nova)
  • The Future World of Martin Bower (special effects model maker)
  • How Frank Hampson worked
  • Creatures from other Worlds
name: Dan Dare Holiday Special 1990

description:
"Welcome, Students"

*New students! New staff! New West Coast Academy! A Classic Avenger is murdered…and everyone’s suspect! Captain America, Luke Cage, and Hawkeye guest-star to…fight the Avengers Academy?
name: Welcome, Students

description:
Cover montage: Dan Dare (Ian Kennedy) - News Team (Jose Ortiz) - Doomlord (Heinzl) - Manix (Carmona)

  • News Team (art: Phil Gascoine)
  • Manix (art: Geoff Senior)
  • Doomlord - quiz page
  • The Collector - Fools' Cargo! (art: Ron Turner)
  • Epics of Sport - Challenge of the Channel (classic reprint)
  • Paco (art: John Stokes)
  • Dan Dare - Stowaway (art: Oliver Frey)
  • Epics of Sport - Moifaa the Unconquerable (classic reprint)
  • The Multi-Mobile (text story)
  • Luke Hackett's The Hand game
  • Epics of Sport - The First Marathon (classic reprint)
  • Joe Soap (art: John Vernon)
  • Crowe Street Comp. (art: Ron Turner)
name: Eagle Holiday Special 1984

Volume 5 Issue 03

Stories in this issue...

Airboy

The Heap

The Lease Says...

The Model Builders with Airboy

Robbers' Roost

Napoleon's Spy

The Flying Fool

Off The Roof of the World

Swivel-Gun Leslie

Corny Corner

Hustler Burns Soldier of Fortune

GET READY FOR THE MOST EARTH SHATTERING, WORLD DESTROYING, INSURANCE-RATE HIKING, EVENT IN MARVEL HISTORY SINCE THE LAST ONE! Wyatt Cenac and Elliott Kalan of “The Daily Show” lead a cavalcade of comedy’s finest minds to answer the questions about the Marvel Universe you were ashamed to ask! This Fall, the Marvel U will be rocked down to its spandex wearing core! Be ashamed. Be VERY ashamed! #shameitself
name: Chapter 43: The Agenda Objective Domination Symposium of Blood

description: After all he's done, everything he's lived through... how does Invincible pick up the pieces and continue on as if nothing has changed? The answer is... he can't.
The Marvel Universe holds a wake for Bucky Barnes ... Fear Itself forever altered the life of Captain America, see how!
name: Captain America

description: The Duck Knight has returned, he's solved the Crisis on Infinite Darkwings, and he's withstood the F.O.W.L. Disposition. With all these Darkwing epics in the bag, will the purple powerhouse of peace be able to deal with Campaign Carnage? It's a super-powered stampede as waves and waves of brand new baddies pop up all over St. Canard, in the midst of a mayoral race you have to see to believe! How many more meta human menaces are gonna show up to crash Darkwing's political party? You’ll have to read this volume to find out! Special Bonus Material: includes the DARKWING DUCK ANNUAL featuring a story by DARKWING DUCK creator Tad Stones himself!
name: Campaign Carnage

description: Still reeling from the Harmory job, Deathstroke seeks answers from a super villain arms manufacturer. But when Slade storms the weapon maker's fortress, he finds himself face to face with a new threat known only as "Legacy" and a plot to manipulate Slade that runs far deeper than he could ever have imagined!
name: Legacy

description: Television's original reluctant vampire is back! Barnabas Collins is re-adjusting to life under his vampiric curse. Haunted by terrifying dreams of his age-old lover and nemesis, Angelique, and fighting his bloodlust, Barnabas fears that danger lies ahead for all who live at Collinwood. Meanwhile, Barnabas' ally and trusted friend Dr. Julia Hoffman is harboring secrets of her own...

Gabriel Hardman Hot on the heels of BOOM!'s sold-out, best-selling Planet of the Apes ongoing series comes a brand new four-issue mini co-written and drawn by Gabriel Hardman! Best known for his series-defining work on Hulk and Agents of ATLAS, and his storyboard work on such hit films as Christopher Nolan's Inception, Hardman and writer Corinna Sara Bechko (Heathentown, Fear Itself: The Home Front) bring you Betrayal of the Planet of the Apes! Taking place during the continuity of the original seminal fan-favorite film, the feared and respected General Aleron finds himself at the center of a conspiracy that could transform ape/human relations! Aleron's journey puts him face to face with...Dr. Zaius! A not-to-be-missed mini-series with story and art that is sure to make you go ape!

has_staff_review.name: Betrayal of the Planet of the Apes #1

volume.name: Betrayal of the Planet of the Apes

description:
The red-hot, sold-out five-issue miniseries from Geoff Johns and Andy Kubert is back in a new hardcover!

This is Flash Fact: When Barry Allen wakes at his desk, he discovers the world has changed. Family is alive, loved ones are strangers, and close friends are different, gone or worse. It's a world on the brink of a cataclysmic war – but where are Earth's Greatest Heroes to stop it?

It's a place where America's last hope is Cyborg, who hopes to gather the forces of The Outsider, The Secret 7, S!H!A!Z!A!M!, Citizen Cold and other new and familiar-yet-altered faces! It's a world that could be running out of time, if The Flash can't find the villain who altered the time line!

Back Blurb

BARRY ALLEN IS A HERO. He protects the innocent and battles evil as The Flash --- the world's fastest man.

But this is not the world he knew. This is a world where Wonder Woman and Aquaman have plunged millions into the darkness of war...where no human has ever wielded the Green Lantern's light...where Batman has as much on his hands as his enemies do...where no one has ever heard of Superman...

....where the Fastest Man Alive is just another man.

Powerless and alone, Barry Allen remembers reality as it once was. Now he must convince its strange, dangerous heroes --- warped versions of the men and women he once fought alongside --- to rally to his cause and set the world to rights. It will take time, but time is the one thing he doesn't have. Because whether he succeeds or fails...

THE WORLD WILL NEVER BE THE SAME.

The superstar creative team of Geoff Johns (BLACKES NIGHT) and Andy Kubert (BATMAN) proudly present FLASHPOINT --- an unforgettable event that takes the DC Universe past the point of no return!
name: TPB

first_appearance_objects.name: Flashpoint Thomas Wayne's Letter to Bruce

object_credits.name: Flashpoint Thomas Wayne's Letter to Bruce

description: The first of The Boys' two concluding stories begins with a bang, as Vought-American's plans for the White House are pre-empted in nothing short of spectacular style. Butcher prepares for war with the Homelander while MM finally loses it completely- in part 1 of the 6-part "Over the Hill with the Swords of a Thousand Men".
name: Over the Hill with the Swords of a Thousand Men, Part 1

description: ALL-NEW, ALL-EVIL TEAM! If the story starts with bionic detective Misty Knight uniting heroes Black Panther, Paladin and Silver Sable to halt a heist, why will she then cross the line and hire those she once fought? Enter a world of treachery, double-crosses and death when you hear: “Hello, Villain...are you for hire?”
name: Version Two Point One

description: Becky has the chance to ask her "Pa" all the questions she needs to about the sixth gun, but does she receive the answers she seeks? Meanwhile, Gord Cantrell's past is further explored in the abandoned rooms of the plantation estate. A little more light is shed on his stoic and cautious nature and it appears to be connected to General Hume's indoctrination into strange magics in a gruesome manner.
name: Bound, Part 5

description: Suspended from school for putting a bully in the hospital, Luther spends his days figuring out his newfound abilities and getting to know Petra, his new girlfriend. Unfortunately, it’s not going to last long with The Librarian killing his way toward Luther and those that he loves.
name: The Strange Talent of Luther Strode

volume.name: The Strange Talent of Luther Strode

description: Includes a PSA starring Binky

General Ross, a.k.a. Red Hulk, proceeds with his unsanctioned mission to find the mysterious Dagan Shah, the man Rulk believes responsible for the death of a former friend. But as Red and his new ally Machine Man fight through ancient monsters and treacherous terrain, are their answers closer than they even imagined? Wondrous word-slinger Jeff Parker and master draftsman Patch Zircher forge one of the most highly anticipated Hulk stories yet!
name: Hulk of Arabia, Pt. 3: The Shifting Sands

description: In the wake of the events of X-MEN: SCHISM the New Mutants find themselves at a crossroads. A decision needs to be made that will change their lives forever. Featuring fan-favorite artist David Lopez (Hawkeye & Mockingbird, Mystic).
Sin, Crossbones, and Valkeryie race across the globe in search the missing hammers! The Secret Avengers guest-star in a battle against Raizo and an army of zombies!
name: Death Wish!

description: SAVAGE DRAGON IS BACK! Or is he? Special 48-page anniversary issue! A certain green-skinned, fin-headed freak finds himself aboard a spaceship headed for parts unknown and has to begin making sense of his new life and the new reality which surrounds him. Meanwhile on Earth, Malcolm Dragon faces his greatest challenge yet: the omnipotent OverLord! And waiting in the wings--an alien invasion! Plus: Vanguard faces--Universo?
name: The Awakening

description: SWEET TOOTH's most unusual storyline yet, "The Taxidermist," continues. Thacker and his men are taken on a journey deep into the frozen heart of Alaska where the origins of the plague may lie hidden deep below the ice! Jeff Lemire and guest artist Matt Kindt continue their mysterious mini-epic!
name: The Taxidermist Part Two of Three: Taboos

description:
Meet mankind's last hope for survival. He's called The Last, and he hates our guts.

The apocalypse is stopped before it can start, and the Last has taken his place as ruler of Earth. His beneficent rule may not be all that it seems when his siblings' sins begin to surface.
name: The Deal, Part Two

description: The Avengers fight their way across the South China Sea, while Nick Fury hijacks a jet fighter to rendezvous with the team in Madripoor --where their occult adversaries have a hellish gauntlet awaiting them in the garden district of the capital.

Poe's Tales of Mystery features a new full-color comics adaptation of Poe's seminal detective story 'The Murders in the Rue Morgue.' Also 'The Facts in the Case of M. Valdemar,' 'The Man of the Crowd,' and ten more stories and poems by the creator of the mystery genre.
name: Tale of Mystery by Edgar Allan Poe

description: Young heroes gain superhuman abilities when they bond with 99 powerful gemstones. These Noor Stones were forged from the destruction of ancient Baghdad to preserve the wisdom of the ages, and were lost for centuries, but they are being found, one-by-one...
name: Beginnings

description:
While searching a physics lab in New York City for a boy she once sparedafter being ordered to murder his family, X-23 meets a man with a mysterious symbol burned into his forehead. A symbol from her dreams. He slips away before Laura can stop him, and Laura finds herself teaming up with the Future Foundation! After running tests on a machine taken from the same physics lab X-23 had visited, Mr. Fantastic discovers that the device was activated by a signal being emitted from Laura, Sue and Spider-Man - a signal that echoes the energy signature of the Enigma Force, a cosmic entity that selects human hosts to wield its power in times of universal need. An entity that had selected all three heroes for possession in the past. The Enigma Force reveals that his archenemy, the king of Whirldemons, has somehow managed to come to Earth by using the device that Reed took from physics lab.

The Whirldemon King reveals himself and attacks the FF! Just when they think they have the upper hand, the demon inhabits Valeria and gives the heroes a choice : open the portal to his people, or Valeria will die!
name: Chaos Theory, Part 4
